 and Satan play in congregants' lives-not only as objects of belief but as actual agents. It explores the concepts of religious experience and religious ritual, while emphasizing the attributions that people make to the operation of spiritual forces and beings in their lives. Through interviews and field work, Nelson uncovers what religious people themselves see as important about their faith while extending and refining sociological understandings of religious ritual and religious experience.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.18574/nyu/9780814759172.001.0001zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814759172zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814759172/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA